definitions: panel in vehicle roof that slides or tilts open to let in light and air
examples: The sunroof was open during our scenic coastal drive
She closed the sunroof when it started to rain

definitions: cream or lotion applied to skin to protect against harmful ultraviolet rays from the sun
examples: Apply sunscreen every two hours when at the beach
The dermatologist recommended using sunscreen with SPF 50

definitions: light and warmth that comes directly from the sun
examples: The morning sunshine brightened the entire kitchen
Children were playing outside in the warm sunshine

definitions: dark area on the sun's surface caused by intense magnetic activity and appearing cooler than surrounding regions
examples: Scientists observed several large sunspots through the telescope
Sunspot activity follows an eleven-year cycle pattern

definitions: informal word for supper or a small evening meal
examples: We had a quick sup before heading to the theater
Join us for a simple sup at seven o'clock

definitions: regular payment made into a fund by an employee toward a future pension
examples: The company contributes nine percent to employee superannuation
She checked her superannuation balance before planning retirement

definitions: device that increases an engine's power by forcing extra air into the combustion chamber
examples: The sports car featured a powerful supercharger system
Installing a supercharger significantly improved the vehicle's acceleration

definitions: computer with exceptional processing power used for complex calculations and scientific research
examples: The weather bureau uses a supercomputer for climate modeling
Scientists ran the simulation on the university's new supercomputer

definitions: taxonomic category in biology that groups related families of organisms sharing common characteristics
examples: Cats and dogs belong to different superfamilies within Carnivora
The superfamily includes several extinct and living species

definitions: star of enormous size and luminosity that represents a late stage in stellar evolution
examples: Betelgeuse is a red supergiant in the constellation Orion
The supergiant will eventually explode as a supernova

definitions: fictional character with extraordinary abilities who fights evil and protects people
examples: The superhero saved the city from the alien invasion
Children dressed as their favorite superheroes for Halloween

definitions: act or position of managing and overseeing an organization or activity with authority
examples: The project proceeded smoothly under her careful superintendence
Superintendence of the construction site required daily inspections

definitions: person who manages or oversees an organization or department
person responsible for maintenance and management of a building
examples: The school superintendent announced new educational policies
The police superintendent addressed concerns about neighborhood safety
Call the superintendent about the broken heating system
The building superintendent lives on the ground floor

definitions: quality or state of being better, greater, or more important than others
examples: The team demonstrated their superiority throughout the tournament
His attitude of superiority made him unpopular with colleagues

definitions: grammatical form expressing the highest degree of a quality or the word expressing such degree
examples: 'Best' is the superlative form of 'good'
The critic used many superlatives to describe the performance

definitions: person of extraordinary ability or achievement
examples: He worked like a superman to finish the project
You can't be a superman and do everything yourself

definitions: large self-service store selling groceries and household goods
examples: We do our weekly shopping at the local supermarket
The supermarket offers fresh produce and bakery items daily

definitions: highly successful and internationally recognized fashion model commanding top fees
examples: The supermodel appeared on magazine covers worldwide
Several supermodels walked the runway at fashion week

definitions: phenomena or manifestations that cannot be explained by natural laws or science
examples: The movie featured supernatural creatures and ghostly apparitions
Many cultures have beliefs in supernatural forces and spirits

definitions: person or thing beyond the usual or required number
examples: The theater hired supernumeraries for the crowd scenes
Several supernumerary staff members assisted during the conference

definitions: placement of one thing on top of another or the principle in physics where waves combine
examples: The geologist studied the superposition of rock layers
Quantum superposition allows particles to exist in multiple states

definitions: country with dominant influence in international affairs
exceptional or superhuman ability
examples: The United States emerged as a superpower after World War II
China's growing economy established it as a global superpower
Flying is a common superpower in comic books
If you could have any superpower, what would it be?

definitions: letter, figure, or symbol written or printed above the normal line of text
examples: The footnote number appeared as a superscript after the quote
Mathematical exponents are written in superscript format

definitions: extremely famous and successful performer or athlete known internationally
examples: The basketball superstar signed autographs for hours
She became a superstar after her breakthrough album

definitions: belief or practice based on fear or ignorance rather than reason or scientific knowledge
examples: Breaking a mirror is considered bad luck in many superstitions
His superstition about black cats made him change routes

definitions: part of a building or ship above its foundation or deck
examples: Workers began constructing the superstructure after completing the foundation
The ship's superstructure included the bridge and command center

definitions: main antagonist in stories who possesses extraordinary powers and opposes superheroes
examples: The supervillain plotted to take over the entire world
Every superhero movie needs a compelling supervillain character

definitions: act of watching over and directing work or activities of others
examples: Supervising the construction project required constant attention
She spent the morning supervising the new employee training

definitions: action of overseeing and directing activities or people to ensure proper completion
examples: Children played outside under adult supervision
The project requires close supervision to meet quality standards

definitions: evening meal, typically lighter or more informal than dinner
examples: We had soup and sandwiches for supper
Grandmother always served supper at six o'clock sharp

definitions: act of taking the place of someone or something by force or strategy
examples: Digital technology is supplanting traditional printing methods
The supplanting of old customs happened gradually over decades

definitions: something added to complete or enhance something else
pill or powder containing nutrients taken to improve diet
examples: The textbook includes a supplement with extra practice problems
The magazine published a special supplement on healthy living
She takes vitamin D supplements during winter months
Athletes often use protein supplements after workouts

definitions: process of adding something extra to enhance or complete, especially nutrients to diet
examples: Calcium supplementation may benefit people with osteoporosis
The program includes supplementation of basic skills training

definitions: action of asking or begging for something earnestly or humbly
examples: The prisoner made a supplication for mercy to the judge
Their supplications for aid went unanswered for weeks

definitions: person or company that provides goods or services to businesses or consumers
examples: The restaurant changed suppliers to get fresher ingredients
We need to find a reliable supplier for office equipment

definitions: act of providing or making available something that is needed or wanted
examples: The company specializes in supplying medical equipment to hospitals
Supplying fresh water to remote areas remains a challenge

definitions: act of giving help, encouragement, or approval to someone or something
examples: Supporting local businesses helps strengthen the community economy
The foundation focuses on supporting education in rural areas

definitions: belief or idea that something may be true but lacks proof or certainty
examples: His theory was based on supposition rather than evidence
The detective's supposition proved correct after further investigation

definitions: action of forcibly stopping, preventing, or inhibiting something from happening or being expressed
examples: The suppression of free speech violates democratic principles
Doctors prescribed medication for appetite suppression

definitions: device that reduces or eliminates something, especially sound from a firearm
examples: The rifle was fitted with a suppressor for stealth operations
The electrical suppressor prevented interference with other devices

definitions: person who believes a particular group is superior and should dominate others
examples: The supremacist ideology was rejected by mainstream society
Historians studied the rise of supremacist movements

definitions: state of being supreme or having the most power, authority, or status
examples: The empire maintained naval supremacy for two centuries
The team's supremacy in the league went unchallenged

definitions: person in charge with the highest rank or greatest authority in an organization
examples: The fashion supremo launched a new designer collection
As marketing supremo, she transformed the company's image

definitions: chapter of the Quran, the Islamic holy book
examples: The imam recited a sura during the evening prayer
Each sura contains verses called ayat

definitions: extra charge or payment added to the usual cost of something
examples: The airline imposed a fuel surcharge on all tickets
Credit card payments incur a three percent surcharge

definitions: person who takes responsibility for another's debt or obligation
examples: His uncle acted as surety for the business loan
The court required a surety before granting bail

definitions: mass of foam formed by waves breaking on a shore or reef
examples: The surf was too rough for swimming today
Seabirds searched for food in the foaming surf

definitions: act of coming up to or appearing at the surface
material used for covering roads or paths
examples: The whale's surfacing created a spectacular water display
Divers practiced controlled surfacing techniques
The road needs new surfacing after winter damage
Workers completed the surfacing of the parking lot

definitions: long narrow board used for riding waves in the sport of surfing
examples: She waxed her surfboard before heading to the beach
The vintage surfboard hung on the restaurant wall
